-- Fifth Third mortgage unit to pay $1.5 mln in bias case -Justice Dept.
-- By Aruna Viswanatha
-- Thu Aug 07, 2014 04:23PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, Aug 7 (Reuters) - The mortgage unit of Fifth Third Bancorp <FITB.O> will pay $1.5 million to resolve allegations it discriminated against borrowers who received disability benefits, the U.S. Justice Department said on Thursday.

